// Stdlib: `@optimized fn simulate_trajectory` (`std.trajectory.fns`)
//
// PRD: docs/prds/v0_3/trajectory-input-shaping.md §6.1, §11 Phase 3 θ / π.
//
// WHY this is a separate module (phase-order, mirrors std.modal.analysis.fns):
//   In the Reify compiler, `phase_functions` runs before `phase_entities`
//   within a single module. `simulate_trajectory`'s placeholder body
//   constructs `EndEffectorTrack()` (a no-arg ctor — like `ModalResult()` in
//   modal_analysis_fns.ri, which likewise carries no per-field defaults), which
//   requires `EndEffectorTrack`'s `structure def` to already be resolved in the
//   prelude template registry. When the function lives alongside the struct
//   definition in `std.trajectory`, `phase_functions` runs before the
//   `EndEffectorTrack` `structure def` is processed and the type is not yet
//   resolvable.
//
//   Solution: declare the struct types in `std.trajectory` (loaded first),
//   then declare `simulate_trajectory` here in `std.trajectory.fns` (loaded
//   immediately after). By the time `phase_functions` processes this file,
//   `EndEffectorTrack`, `Profile`, and `ModalResult` are all in the prelude
//   template registry and the ctor resolves. Same split + rationale as the
//   `std.modal.analysis` / `std.modal.analysis.fns` split
//   (modal_analysis_fns.ri:6-20, esc-3851-32).

// ── simulate_trajectory ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// `@optimized("trajectory::simulate")` causes the engine to insert a
// ComputeNode with target == "trajectory::simulate" rather than body-inlining.
// The trampoline lives at crates/reify-eval/src/trajectory_ops.rs (task π); it
// marshals (profile, mech, modal) through the pure forward-pass simulator
// (`reify-stdlib/src/trajectory/{trampoline,simulate}.rs`) and returns a real
// `EndEffectorTrack` `Value`. The placeholder body below is NEVER evaluated on
// the registered path — dispatch replaces the whole call with the ComputeNode.
//
// Signature deviation from PRD §6.1 `(profile, mechanism, modal_result)`:
//   `mech : Real` — the kinematic `Mechanism` type lives in `std.kinematic`,
//     which is loaded AFTER `std.trajectory(.fns)` in the prelude sequence and
//     so is unavailable here. Uses the bare `Real` placeholder, the uniform
//     convention across this module (`PiecewisePolynomialProfile.mechanism :
//     Real`, `EndEffectorTrack.mechanism : Real` — trajectory.ri:261,319).
//     TODO(mechanism-type): tighten to `Mechanism` once the kinematic-
//     completion PRD lands.
//   `modal : ModalResult` — in-prelude (`std.modal.analysis` loads earlier).
//
// Unregistered-engine fallback: if the "trajectory::simulate" trampoline is not
// registered, the engine body-inlines this placeholder (+ an Error diagnostic),
// yielding an empty `EndEffectorTrack()`. Every test needing REAL dispatch must
// call `reify_eval::compute_targets::register_compute_fns(&mut engine)` first
// (plan design-decision-10).
@optimized("trajectory::simulate")
pub fn simulate_trajectory(p: Profile, mech: Real, modal: ModalResult) -> EndEffectorTrack {
    EndEffectorTrack()
}
